tal days and nearly reaching three months. Originally generated as 3 Load ports USG, 4 disports Brazil, and 2 disports Uruguay, the voyage was eventually changed to add another discharge port in Uruguay increased freight but of course added days and lowered the TCE. With the additional days, there were 21 days on demurrage at $34k/day. Port expenses were higher than generated due to the additional port added, but the additional freight did cover this.\n\nThe entire voyage, Tricon wanted to maximize intake, leaving us with no choice but to bunker offshore after loading due to draft restrictions. The weather was very rough, so we waited at GOLA for almost four days idle. The vessel\u0027s deep draft and heavy currents enroute to Itaqui affected her laden passage. More info on this below in improvements.Voyage was generated at 5% weather, however actual laden weather factor was 22%. Part of this was definitely weather, but we should also consider that this was the most cargo we\u0027ve really seen loaded on an IMOIIMAX where the Laden draft was 12.5 m and 45,000 MT of cargo onboard after 3rd load port. Laden speed was fixed at 13kts and vessel averaged 10.81 kts. In the future, we should ensure voyages with USG to Brazil have a higher percentage of weather factored into the generation."},{"modifiedDate":"2023-06-02T14:59:30.283","modifiedByFull":"Land, Macy","remark":"Updated port costs for Uruguay. Still waiting on tugs for a couple of ports."},{"modifiedDate":"2023-06-02T15:08:43.823","modifiedByFull":"Land, Macy","remark":"I miscalculated deumurrage.Amended now."},{"modifiedDate":"2023-04-20T18:45:25.453","modifiedByFull":"Land, Macy","remark":"Days and time updated."},{"modifiedDate":"2023-04-19T18:53:45.163","modifiedByFull":"Land, Macy","remark":"Demurrage was overstated."},{"modifiedDate":"2023-04-05T12:17:40.843","modifiedByFull":"Land, Macy","remark":"Vsl experiencing heavy current enroute to Brazil. Also has a very deep draft restricting vessel\u0027s speed"},{"modifiedDate":"2023-03-29T15:05:19.55","modifiedByFull":"Land, Macy","remark":"Estimated 8 days of demurrage. To be updated as voyage progresses."},{"modifiedDate":"2023-03-30T13:26:30.38","modifiedByFull":"Land, Macy","remark":"Delay in bunkering due to weather. Time for our account - About 4 days. Had to bunker offshore as loadports not ideal plus had to bunker after loading due to drafts."},{"modifiedDate":"2023-02-22T22:58:13.757","modifiedByFull":"Fdemosteyrin, Manuel","remark":"Tricon CSS USG/Brazil-Uruguay 10-16 Feb - Max cargo CSS"}],"offhireList":[],"tcNumber":null,"tcOutIdEncrypted":null,"tcReletDetail":null}